				<div>
					Posts: 2,389
				</div>
				<div><!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_reputation -->
<img class="inlineimg" src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/images/reputation/reputation_pos.gif" alt="JanSorensen is on a distinguished road" border="0" />
<!-- END TEMPLATE: postbit_reputation --></div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Cleric numbers on raids.</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>This is a topic that is often debated. Both because it pertains very much to our class and because I find that not all such debates are entirely factual am I opening the debate here (yet again). I will try to consider various suggested solutions for validity – unfortunately without reaching any sort of perfect solution. I don’t have a clear agenda with this post except to start a hopefully enlightening debate. I do realise that this post is rather unstructured – possibly because I don’t have a clear agenda. I hope its still interesting reading.<br />
<br />
I will only concern myself with raids that have a 54 char limit. Unlimited raids don’t really pose a problem – while considering different limits is outside the scope of this post.<br />
<br />
The main question to ask would be:<br />
If you have 53 people already – and one of each class sitting ready to fill the 54th spot (all 16 equal in every aspect except for their class) – when in terms of clerics already in the raid does /should it become less desirable to take a cleric than another class.<br />
<br />
I believe there are two main situations<br />
A) Winning a raid encounter for the very first time (for me that could be Zun’Muram)<br />
B) Redoing an already won encounter (for me that could be Inktuta)<br />
as well as two main issues (as seen from the raid’s point of view)<br />
a) Having any chance at winning<br />
b) Being (almost) sure of winning<br />
<br />
When dealing with situation A, the issue the issue that comes to mind with be a – while situation B often concerns itself more with issue b.<br />
<br />
A+b is hardly worth considering (winning a brand new encounter easily on the first attempt) – while B+a definitely is a concern (having to cancel a raid of an already won encounter for lack of numbers).<br />
<br />
With this in mind lets consider some points of view (they are made up – but I believe it would be possible to find someone sharing either of them).<br />
<br />
1) There are 54 slots on raids – so on average there should be 54/16 clerics present – so 3-4 clerics.<br />
2) Healers are 1 in 4 arch types – and clerics are 1 in 3 healers. Hence 54/12 or 4-5 clerics is reasonable on average.<br />
3) Clerics are a raid class – while other classes are less so. Accept that and consider 6-7 clerics on average reasonable.<br />
4) Clerics are made for raids – 9-10 clerics on average is reasonable.<br />
I won’t judge these statements – except to say that they all carry a certain amount of truth.<br />
<br />
<br />
(continued)</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
