	<div align="center">
		<div class="page" style="width:95%; text-align:left">
			<div style="padding:0px 0px 0px 0px">

<!-- END TEMPLATE: spacer_open --><div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px">

<table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
<tr>
	
		<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" >		
			<!-- status icon and date -->
			<a name="post231406"><img class="inlineimg" src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/images/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a>
			08-31-2004, 10:28 AM
			
			<!-- / status icon and date -->				
		</td>
		<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">
			&nbsp;
			#<a href="showpost.php?s=f79ed02054a53e811726ed489ea38d1d&amp;p=231406&amp;postcount=2" target="new"><strong>2</strong></a>
		</td>
	
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
	<td class="alt2" width="175">
			
			<div id="postmenu_231406">
				
				<a class="bigusername" href="member.php?s=f79ed02054a53e811726ed489ea38d1d&amp;u=1230">JanSorensen</a>
				<script type="text/javascript"> vbmenu_register("postmenu_231406", true); </script>
				
			</div>
			
			<div class="smallfont">Fighting misinformation</div>
			
		
			
			
			<div class="smallfont">
				&nbsp;<br />
				<div>Join Date: Feb 2000</div>
				<div>Location: Denmark</div>
				
				<div>
					Posts: 2,389
				</div>
				<div><!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_reputation -->
<img class="inlineimg" src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/images/reputation/reputation_pos.gif" alt="JanSorensen is on a distinguished road" border="0" />
<!-- END TEMPLATE: postbit_reputation --></div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>As raids are what they are – and need they healing they do – there are two solutions if one subscribes to the notion that “raids needs too many clerics” + one solution to simply lower the healing needed. <br />
A) Make clerics heal better so fewer clerics can do the same job<br />
B) Make other priests better at healing so any priest can do the job.<br />
C) Make raids need less healing.<br />
<br />
Lets tackle C first. The problem here would be that then something other than healing would have to be made harder – or the raids simply got easier which isn’t very desirable.<br />
<br />
A: This is a tricky one. Clerics are presently wanted in large numbers on raids because we are the best at healing. In that sense making clerics even better healers obviously does not make any sense. On the other hand some do argue that the reason so many clerics are needed is because we aren’t good enough. Personally I subscribe to the former view.<br />
<br />
B: As seen purely from a raiding point of view this actually makes a good deal of sense. However, then we have the problem of balance outside raiding which risks getting upset by such a change. That leads to the idea of heals that are somehow restricted so they are only/mostly useful in a raid setting – but many druids/shaman fight that notion. In particular many of them fight the idea of getting a raid only CH. Personally I find that a very good solution though. I would give druids/shaman a larger role in healing on raids – while simultaneously freeing clerics to use our many other types of heals more rather then chaining us to the chain.<br />
<br />
<br />
For most encounters I personally find that the threshold in numbers of clerics present to have a chance at win the first time is reasonable – with some notable exceptions that require too many (subjectively speaking). However, what I find worse is that the number of clerics desirable to raise the odds of winning (mind, that is taking a cleric over another class) is too high. We simply stack too well on raids. So, while beating for example Inktuta for the first time with 6 clerics is certainly possible – it’s far more desirable to have 10 or even 12. Once the fight has been won a few times the number needed as well as wanted often goes slightly down – but the preferred number often stays quite high. Thus, often I find that the “absolutely needed” number is near reasonable – but the “desired” number remains too high.<br />
<br />
A very radical idea would be to limit raids in a manner so that no more than 6 of any class could be present. This would certainly fix a great deal of balance problems – but it would create a huge social problem. Hence it’s sadly not an acceptable solution even though it would be the perfect solution in terms of balancing raids.<br />
<br />
<br />
As said earlier – this was quite unstructured – I apologise for this hoping its still an interesting read.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
