		<!-- message -->
		<div>A hardcoded limit on classes would be interesting, but not even worth discussing with the current position of the game. <br />
<br />
I think your correct on the "more healers = better chance of winning" at least to a point. No one likes to lose, so that leads to a feeling of reliance on the massive healer numbers.  <br />
<br />
I would not advocate sadldling druids/shaman with a raid only CH. In general we dont like it, why should we foist the job off onto someone else instead of trying to change the reasons for the job in the first place? The downside is, thats much easier said than done. So yes, in a short term sense, raid only CH for druids/shaman could lead to more immediate success raid-wise. However, what does that do to the Cleric role outside of raids? I think it would still have some effect, in a sense establishing a mindset of .. "Well, I can be a druid, gain more abilities outside of the raid scene and still serve 2 vital roles in the raid now." I dont think that the two cases can exist as mutually exclusive elements. (IE even an upgrade targeted and limited to raid only situations will play some impact in character choice/creation/power. Making the other two classes even _more_ appealing if they can double-up as chainbot in high end content)<br />
<br />
To me its a Catch-22. <br />
<br />
Nice points/post though.</div>
