	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I think some of the encounter designs certainly emphasize less healing and more DPS or CCing(root/mez/kite), however many of those mini-encounters are wrapped into larger instanced raids which at some point in time do require large amounts of healing.<br />
<br />
For example we did Kelek in Inktuta just for a couple loots with no more than 35 people, 7 of which were clerics.  1 out of 5 I would say is our typical makeup of clerics lately, 1 out of 6 during the great attendence we had in PoTime with raids being 55+ people.  Anyways, that Kelek fight took 35 minutes from spawn to win.  Sure had we not had every last cleric, we most probably would have lost too many at some points and wiped(well it is pretty hard to totally wipe on that).  Though, given 5 or 6 more DPS and one less cleric, with proper group tuning that fight easily could be cut into half its duration.  Mites and the DT event in Inktu'ta are also not neccessarily cleric dependant.  I guess on mites if someone screws up and you find yourself with 12 people in a room and 4ish mites, a 3rd cleric would certainly help out.  But if things go as planned, there is very little need for cleric healing.  Inktu'ta is pretty lax on clerics until the Noq fight.<br />
<br />
Uqua is more or less the same though the encounters aren't quite as different leading up to Barxt.  A few extra clerics certainly helps, but if those golems respawn while fighting the 2 mini's, it's over.  I certainly don't mean to undermine the use of clerics on the traps though, a few extra clerics certainly help, but with proper aggro control on everyone's part they are oftentimes a breeze with minimal healing required.<br />
<br />
Even in Tacvi there are many original events, though I'm a bit reluctant to go into too much depth but the balance guy and the exploding adds guy certainly favor aspects other than healing to win.  That charm guy though, wtf were they thinking!  But as we all know, the first Pixxt thing requires a lot of guild coordination and execution along with as many free clerics as you can find to pick up the slack.  <br />
<br />
So my semi-conclusion thing is, it's kind of weird how they (imho) seriously put a lot of effort into making challenging fights that aren't all healing based, just to throw in an insanely attentive encounter for clerics.  At the same time though, none of them really go out and make guilds say, we need to recruit more encs to beat this one guy.  Though if they start mixing around these types of events that stress different classes, it may very well force guilds to have a "balanced" mixed of talented people in all catagories.  This might be a blessing, but it may very well be a curse.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
