		<div>We love you too Thecklos, but keep the retard comments to yourself, your no winning any points with insults.<br />
<br />
the 54/16 ratio is fine if that is what content is designed to support in a raid. obviously it does in fact work in every aspect except healing. This is why so many people are pushing for a healing balance similer to the tank balance. I've grown indiffrent to it mostly, since I no longer raid, I see druids and shaman filling in all the time where clerics tread, and its a good balance. that same balance could be applied to raids with some work and effort.<br />
<br />
However, as has been said before, how many actually want that kind of change?  I cant think of any druid or shaman that wants to wear the CH chain shackles, but at the same time, almost every one that posts talks about how they need more healing (to me what they mean is give us enough, but no so much we have to heal on raids too, or to justify nerfs)<br />
<br />
People mix/max to the limit of class avalibility. not even the best guilds in game could always field exactly the forces they wanted, pretty close to be sure, but never "8 clerics 8 wizards 8 rogues, we are set"<br />
This is the main reason why when asked how to make shaman and druids capable of raid healing I suggested a 95% capability. that way min maxing isnt an issue because there is not enough veriance in ability to make it worth the time or effort. this would also obviously require the largest change to all three classes outside of healing as well, which makes it mostly unacceptable.<br />
<br />
It can be done though, and it just means making sure the balance of tools is worth it outside of healing. For instance, if druids were left as is outside of healing, then clerics would need something to offer to a raid that is as valueble as that druids DPS while clearing trash (since the healing isnt going to be critical at that phase)and as useful as the druid utility (damage shields, ports, resist buffs etc, we are already pretty close here in a raid)<br />
<br />
as far as how much would get broken by major changes, I agree its going to be a lot, but most of that will be older content that isnt critical to game health any longer (who cares if a group of druids can heal a tank for vindi when a group of high end players can take him out anyway)</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
