				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Discombobulation</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">The dps of mobs need to have a set cap per expansion to prevent needing heavy amounts of healing. You "beta" an encounter, and if the dps is too high for high end people then lower it <img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/images/smilies/banghead.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Beat head" class="inlineimg" /> . Then you get an idea of what the basic number of "too much" is, and don't go over that in the expansion.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<!-- END TEMPLATE: bbcode_quote --><br />
<br />
Do this, and people will figure out the mob dps and simply adjust their raid to include 1 to 2 priests or clerics (depending on healing parity) more than they need to offset the basic dps period.  The reason they'll always take a couple extra is for things like DI, and coverage over dead clerics.  All this would do is tell people exactly how much healing is required for every encounter.  Actually it's already sort of like this now, it's just that currently max healing needed on a tank == about 6 clerics, then you also need some more clerics for things like DI, healing the healers, rez duty, etc.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36220" target="_blank">Thecklos</a> <br />
Archon of Brell<br />
Dol Amroth<br />
Rodcet Nife
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
