	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I believe that the core problem is<br />
- many (most) encounters <i>get easier</i> by replacing other classes by clerics up to a very high number of clerics - while nearly no encounters get easier by replacing a cleric with any other class unless you have near nill of that class.<br />
<br />
with a secondary problem of <br />
- some (few) encounters <i>require</i> too many clerics(healers).<br />
<br />
As for the ratio of healers to others. I find that having 1/3 be priests+paladins is reasonable (thats 2 healers per group). Thats indeed more than 4/16 - but I am fine with that. I also find that 6 clerics + 4 of each of druids, shaman and paladins is an ok comprimise to aim for as the optimum. What I do not know is how to reasonably make clerics stack less well so having 10 clerics doesnt make it even easier. Mind, even being a cleric I am not terribly happy with us being in so high demand for raids.<br />
<br />
Giving other priests a raid only CH (functionally if not technically), Paladins a clicky rez, shaman DI and druids a (small) group heal would be a start though - except that clerics would still stack damn well.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
